                                        <property name="focusable">1</property>
                                        <property name="tooltip-text" translatable="1">Quality. Setting quality = 100 gives lossless compression (note that this can be quite slow). Other quality values work in the same way as JPEG quality, but there is no direct read-across (the same quality value will not give exactly the same visual quality or file size as it would for a JPEG file).

    NOTE: lossy compression gives bad results when saving linear data owing to the very high dynamic range, however lossless compression offers a smaller filesize than TIFF compression at the expense of being slower and not providing the metadata that is available with TIFF.</property>
                                        <property name="text" translatable="1">100</property>
